                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Dear Mr. Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>Hearts&#45;ease is<lb/> the boon which friends desire<lb/> for each other&#44; and I have<lb/> endeavored&#44; in choosing this<lb/> emblem&#44; to convey true regard.<lb/>  When you wear these slippers<lb/> you will look up as well as<lb/> down to understand what<lb/> they are meant to express&#59; you<lb/> will search in the spiritual<lb/> world for the aspirations<lb/> and counsel which&#44; uttered<lb/> by you in the presence of<lb/> numbers&#44; have aided one<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>soul&#44; at least&#58; that one<lb/> desires to gratefully record<lb/> its indebtedness.<lb/></p>
            <p>With much respect<lb/>
                Your sincere friend<lb/>
                Mary M. Cohen<lb/></p>
                
            <p>1828 Rittenhouse Square.<lb/>
                November 21<hi rend="sup">st</hi> 1879.<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais<lb/>
                546 North Fifth St<lb/></p>
        </body>
